I think the issue is caused by `||mmstat.com^` in DNS filter which blocks the script `https://log.mmstat.com/eg.js` which is already unblocked in non-DNS filter. The script URL content is simply

```adb
window.goldlog=(window.goldlog||{});goldlog.Etag="iFo0IJ31biwCAZJGcWdvaDo0";goldlog.stag=1;
```

on my side. The website's script simply checks the value of `goldlog.Etag` if there's no `cna` cookie yet:

```js
function f() {
  if (this.cna) {
    return this.cna;
  } else if (this.cookie.getCookie("cna")) {
    this.cna = this.cookie.getCookie("cna");
    return this.cna;
  } else if (window.goldlog && window.goldlog.Etag) {
    this.cna = window.goldlog.Etag;
    return this.cna;
  } else {
    this.loadfile("https://log.mmstat.com/eg.js", "js");
    return null;
  }
}
```

so this works at least for me:

```adb
youku.com#%#//scriptlet('trusted-set-constant', 'goldlog.Etag', '"iFo0IJ31biwCAZJGcWdvaDo0"')
```

However I'm not sure if that value is stable or not.

